Setting Screen Resolution

   Selection of the screen size depends very much upon the graphic being loaded or created.  The SCREEN SIZE option pulled from the PROJECT menu lets you define the correct display mode. There are four basic display modes: interlaced, non-interlaced, low resolution and high resolution. The higher the numbers, the better the image quality of the figure. These modes are combined as follows:
